News - Date: 10 February 2018 Written by: Kaizer Nengovhela / Viewed: 138 Two suspects who allegedly killed a police officer in October last year will remain in custody. Hangwelani Mulovhedzi and Khathutshelo Nemutandani allegedly shot and killed Lt-Col Phineas Mamatsiari at Dzwerani. They appeared in the Thohoyandou Magistrate’s Court last Wednesday and the case was postponed to 26 April for further investigation. Lt-Col Phineas Mamatsiari had just arrived home from work when he was attacked at Dzwerani outside Thohoyandou. The two suspects allegedly stole Mamatsiari’s unmarked police vehicle after shooting him but were cornered when they reached Thohoyandou.  A shoot-out ensued between the suspects and the police. Mulovhedzi was arrested while Nemutandani allegedly escaped. During the shoot-out, Const Livhuwani Budeli was shot and wounded. Nemutandani was on the run for three months before he was arrested two weeks ago. The two men now face five charges, including murder, attempted murder, armed robbery and the possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition.  Kaizer Nengovhela started writing stories for Limpopo Mirror more than a decade ago, in 2 000. Prior to that he had a five year stint at Phala-Phala FM as sports presenter. In 2005 Kaizer received an award from the province's premier as Best Sports Presenter. The same year he was also nominated as Best Sports Reporter by the Makhado Municipality. Kaizer was awarded the Mathatha Tsedu award in 2014.  Email: kaizerdo@webmail.co.za